        <mxCell id="A49KD2nKRxiiyZH7kdmM-35" parent="A49KD2nKRxiiyZH7kdmM-32" style="text;strokeColor=default;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=4;spacingRight=4;overflow=hidden;points=[[0,0.5],[1,0.5]];portConstraint=eastwest;rotatable=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" value="&lt;div&gt;Movement&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;Slow motion timer when controlling objects&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;Using one stick for character and another stick for moving elements&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;instead of having another input, when the character goes near the element, that element&#39;s attribute affects the character&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;earth is grabbable&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;earth lets you lift with it, and then actually jump off, simulating double jump,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;jump is active by default&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;pressing down pushed earth down&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;defensive stance&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;water is grabbable&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;spits from legs/mouth forward&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;debuff stance&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Air is evasive stance&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Fire is DOT stance&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;attack mode&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;water slices, like a sword&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;earth moves things around&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;air pushes back&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;fire shoots and burns&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;" vertex="1">
